The '''Yangon Heritage Trust''' ({{lang-my|ရန်ကုန်အမွေအနှစ် ထိန်းသိမ်းစောင့်ရှောက်ရေးအဖွဲ့}}; abbreviated '''YHT''') is a [[non-governmental organisation]] founded by [[Thant Myint-U]] to conserve historic buildings in [[Yangon]] (formerly Rangoon), the former capital of [[Burma]].<ref name="robinson-2012-03-09">{{cite news|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/366b4332-69b5-11e1-8996-00144feabdc0.html#axzz2g4JkxJTa|title=Myanmar pushes to save colonial buildings|last=Robinson|first=Gwen|date=9 March 2012|work=Financial Times|accessdate=27 September 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.irrawaddy.org/archives/5789|title=Conservation Strategy Drafted for Historic Rangoon|last=Hpyo Wai Tha|date=6 June 2012|work=The Irrawaddy|accessdate=27 September 2013}}</ref> Yangon has Asia's largest collection of colonial-era buildings.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nationmultimedia.com/life/The-race-is-on-in-Yangon-30212999.html|title=The race is on in Yangon|last=KYAW YE LYNN|author2=PETER JANSSEN |work=DEUTSCHE PRESSE-AGENTUR|accessdate=27 September 2013}}</ref> The Trust has proposed to designate small zones within the city centre (particularly in [[Downtown Yangon]]) as heritage areas and envisions a joint public-private collaboration whereby private investors restore heritage buildings for commercial use while maintaining the character of the areas.<ref name="robinson-2012-03-09"/> The Trust also advocates a conservation plan led by the [[private sector]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.mmtimes.com/2012/news/619/news61901.html|title=Historic Yangon cityscape thrown a lifeline|last=Kean|first=Thomas|date=19 March 2012|work=Myanmar Times|accessdate=27 September 2013}}</ref>
In June 2013, [[Philips]] announced a partnership with the Trust to install 200 [[LED]]-lit blue plaques to highlight key cultural heritage sites in the city.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newscenter.philips.com/main/standard/news/press/2013/20130605-Philips-and-Yangon-Heritage-Trust-partner-to-highlight-Yangon's-rich-cultural-heritage.wpd#.UkUZyIakpa8|title=Philips and Yangon Heritage Trust partner to highlight Yangon’s rich cultural heritage sites as part of Philips’ commitment to Myanmar|date=5 June 2013|work=Philips|accessdate=27 September 2013}}</ref>
